<storybody><![CDATA[<p>Ahmedabad, Jun 1 (PTI) Gujarat Government today declared 81 more villages as scarcity-affected owing to acute water shortage there, an official press release said. </p><p>With this latest addition, the total number of scarcity-affected villages in Gujarat has reached 1,347. </p><p>The decision to put these 81 villages of Porbandar district in affected category was taken at a meeting of a sub-committee of ministers formed to assess the scarcity situation. The committee is headed by education minister Bhupendrasinh Chudasama. </p><p>Measures are being taken to provide water and cattle-fodder in affected regions, the government stated. </p><p>As many as 509 villages and 1,042 adjoining localities across Gujarat are getting water through tankers at present. PTI PJT KRK NSD RDS</p>]]></storybody>
